{"lemma":"إِصْبَعَيْ","slug":"إِصْبَعَيْ","root":"ص.ب.ع","root_slug":"ص-ب-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-ب-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n23702","n23705"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A5%D9%90%D8%B5%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"finger, toe","examples":[{"text":"أَوْ كَصَيِّبٍ مِنَ السَّمَاءِ فِيهِ ظُلُمَاتٌ وَرَعْدٌ وَبَرْقٌ يَجْعَلُونَ أَصَابِعَهُمْ فِي آذَانِهِم مِنَ الصَّوَاعِقِ حَذَرَ الْمَوْتِ","english":"Or like a rainstorm from the sky, wherein is darkness, thunder and the flash of lightning. They thrust their fingers in their ears by reason of the thunder-claps, for fear of death."},{"text":"كان هناك ولد صغير يتكلّم ويحاول أن يشبّ على أصابعه لينظر من النافذة.","english":"There was a small boy talking and trying to rear on his toes to look through the window."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"piano key"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"popsicle"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"lollipop"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *ʔiṣbaʕ-."},"ipa":["/ʔisˤ.baʕ/","/ʔisˤ.biʕ/","/ʔisˤ.buʕ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n23702","headword_ar":"اصبع","root":"SbE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", followed by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY","text_ar":"عَلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", is said by Freytag, as on the authority of Meyd, to signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a pastor)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fed and managed well"},{"kind":"text","text":"his cattle: but this is perhaps taken from a mistranscription of the saying, mentioned by Meyd,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lilr~aAEiY EalaY maA$iyatahi","text_ar":"لِلرَّاعِى عَلَى مَاشِيَتَهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iSobaEN","text_ar":"اـِصْبَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. infrà.]"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n23705","headword_ar":"اـِصْبَعٌ","root":"SbE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uSobaEN","text_ar":"اُصْبَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uSobuEN","text_ar":"اُصْبُعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iSobiEN","text_ar":"اـِصْبِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSobiEN","text_ar":"اَصْبِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iSobuEN","text_ar":"اـِصْبُعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSobaEN","text_ar":"اَصْبَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSobuEN","text_ar":"اَصْبُعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uSobiEN","text_ar":"اُصْبِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"being thus trebly vowelled, and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"likewise (Msb, K) with every one of the vowellings of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uSobuwEN","text_ar":"اُصْبُوعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also, (Msb, K,) of all which forms the"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1647},{"kind":"text","text":"first is the [only] one commonly known and the one approved by persons of chaste speech, (Msb,) all mentioned by Kr, (K,) and by Lh also on the authority of Yoo, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A finger:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a toe:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA, KL, &c.:) of the fem. gender, (Msb,) or fem. and masc., (S, O, Msb, K, *) but generally fem.: (O, Msb, K: *) pl. (of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ASbE","text_ar":"اصبع"},{"kind":"text","text":", MA)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAbiEu","text_ar":"اَصَابِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and (of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ASbwE","text_ar":"اصبوع"},{"kind":"text","text":", MA)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAbiyEu","text_ar":"اَصَابِيعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (MA, K.) ―         -b2-  One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihimo tuvonaY AlA^aSaAbiEu","text_ar":"بِهِمْ تُثْنَى الاَصَابِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"With"},{"kind":"text","text":"the mention of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"them the fingers are bent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning that they are reckoned as the best, [or among the best,] for the best are not many. (M, on a verse cited in the first paragraph of art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vnY","text_ar":"ثنى"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [See also two similar exs. in the first paragraph of art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hnw","text_ar":"حنو"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HnY","text_ar":"حنى"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lilr~aAEiY EalaY maA$iyatihi A_iSobaEN","text_ar":"لِلرَّاعِى عَلَى مَاشِيَتِهِ اـِصْبَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The pastor has a finger pointing at his cattle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sheep"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has upon his cattle"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an impress of a good state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, * TA;) i. e. they are pointed at with the fingers because of their goodliness and fatness and good tending. (TA.) [See also a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SulobN","text_ar":"صُلْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] And similar to this saying is the prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi mina A@ll~`hi taEaAlaY A_iSobaEN HasanN","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ مِنَ ا@للّٰهِ تَعَالَى اـِصْبَعٌ حَسَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Upon him is, from God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acknowledged be his absolute supremacy,"},{"kind":"text","text":")]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an impress of a good state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Meyd.) And one says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu laHasanu","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَحَسَنُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_iSobaEi fiY maAlihi","text_ar":"الاـِصْبَعِ فِى مَالِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is good in respect of the impress upon his cattle"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"indicative of their state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (IAar, TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN mugil~u AlA_iSobaEi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ مُغِلُّ الاـِصْبَعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is unfaithful, treacherous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perfidious."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, * TA. *) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu A_iSobaEN fiY h`*aA AlA^amori","text_ar":"لَهُ اـِصْبَعٌ فِى هٰذَا الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has a finger in this affair"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b6-  The Prophet said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalobu Almuw^omini","text_ar":"قَلْبُ المُوْمِنِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayona A_iSobaEayoni mino A^aSaAbiEi A@ll~`hi yuqal~ibuhu kayofa $aA='a","text_ar":"بَيْنَ اـِصْبَعَيْنِ مِنْ اَصَابِعِ ا@للّٰهِ يُقَلِّبُهُ كَيْفَ شَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The heart of the believer is between two of the fingers of God: He turneth it about as He pleaseth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O.) ―         -b7-  And a man says, in respect of a difficult affair, when he has been made to have recourse to a strong man, able to bear his burden,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu yaA^otiY Ealayohi biA_iSobiEK waAHidapK","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ يَاْتِى عَلَيْهِ بِاـِصْبِعٍ وَاحِدَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he will make an end of it with one finger"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu yakofiyhi","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ يَكْفِيهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biSugoraY A^aSaAbiEihi","text_ar":"بِصُغْرَى اَصَابِعِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily the smallest of his fingers will suffice him"},{"kind":"text","text":"for its accomplishment; the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus prefixed to the agent being redundant, as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kafaY biA@ll~`hi $ahiydFA","text_ar":"كَفَى بِا@للّٰهِ شَهِيدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and many other instances]. (O.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abuw AlA_iSobaEi","text_ar":"اَبُو الاـِصْبَعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is one of the surnames of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Devil."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaEahu Al$~iyoTaAnu","text_ar":"صَبَعَهُ الشِّيْطَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", above.]) ―         -b9-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iSobaEN","text_ar":"اـِصْبَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A prong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as resembling a finger: so in the S and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hfr","text_ar":"حفر"},{"kind":"text","text":", and in other instances.] ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAbiEu AlfatayaAti","text_ar":"اَصَابِعُ الفَتَيَاتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, TS, K,) in the “ Minháj ” of Ibn-Jezleh"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ASAbE AlftyAn","text_ar":"اصابع الفتيان"},{"kind":"text","text":", [app. a mistranscription,] and in the I,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ASAbE Albunay~aAti","text_ar":"اصابع البُنَيَّاتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Common clinopodium,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wild basil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the sweet-smelling plant called in Pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfaranojamu$ok","text_ar":"الفَرَنْجَمُشْك"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AHn, O, K,) which grows abundantly in the southern parts of Arabia, and is not depastured by any animal. (AHn, O.) ―         -b11-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAbiEu AlEa*aAraY","text_ar":"اَصَابِعُ العَذَارَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A species of grapes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"black,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long, like the acorn, likened to the dyed fingers of virgins;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, O, K; *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the bunch thereof is about a cubit"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in length"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"compact"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so I render"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutadaAxis","text_ar":"مُتَدَاخِس"},{"kind":"text","text":", supposing it to be similar to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dxys","text_ar":"دخيس"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to herbage &c.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the grapes; its raisins are good; and it grows in the Saráh"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~araAp","text_ar":"السَّرَاة"},{"kind":"text","text":"). (AHn, O.) ―         -b12-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAbiEu huromusa","text_ar":"اَصَابِعُ هُرْمُسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The flowers"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuq~aAH","text_ar":"فُقَّاح"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwranojaAn","text_ar":"سُورَنْجَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hermodactylus"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Iris"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Linn.?) now applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meadow-saffron, a species of colchicum"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (O, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the potency of which is like that of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"swrnjAn","text_ar":"سورنجان"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"itself"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b13-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAbiEu firoEawna","text_ar":"اَصَابِعُ فِرْعَونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Certain things"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maraAwiyd","text_ar":"مَرَاوِيد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maraAwid","text_ar":"مَرَاوِد"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuHol","text_ar":"كُحْل"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is applied"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the length of the finger,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"red;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brought from the Sea of El-Hijáz; of proved efficacy for the speedy consolidation of wounds."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b14-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAbiEu SuforN","text_ar":"اَصَابِعُ صُفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The root"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSol","text_ar":"اَصْل"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a certain plant of which the form is like the hand,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"variegated with yellowness and whiteness, hard, and having a little sweetness; and there is a species thereof yellow, with a dust-colour, but without whiteness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA:) so says Ibn-Jezleh: (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is beneficial as a remedy for madness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"diabolical possession, and for poisons,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the sting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bite, of venomous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"noxious, reptiles,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, and it acts as a dissolvent of thick excrescences."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b15-  As a measure,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iSobaEN","text_ar":"اـِصْبَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A digit;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a finger's breadth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"width of six moderate-sized barley-corns;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jariybN","text_ar":"جَرِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forth part of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaboDap","text_ar":"قَبْضَة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh and Msb ibid.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","Msb","K","TA","TS","AHn"]}]}}